            <script is:inline>window.__RAINDROP_DATA__={"bookmarks":[{"title":"mobile-next/mobile-mcp: Model Context Protocol Server for Mobile Automation and Scraping (iOS, Android, Emulators, Simulators and Real Devices)","link":"https://github.com/mobile-next/mobile-mcp","domain":"github.com","tags":[],"note":"","excerpt":"Model Context Protocol Server for Mobile Automation and Scraping (iOS, Android, Emulators, Simulators and Real Devices) - mobile-next/mobile-mcp","created":"2026.03.24"},{"title":"Mobile Device Screenshot | Claude Code Skill","link":"https://mcpmarket.com/es/tools/skills/mobile-device-screenshot","domain":"mcpmarket.com","tags":[],"note":"","excerpt":"Capture and analyze screenshots from iOS Simulators, physical iPhones, and Android devices using Claude Code to debug mobile UI and layout issues.","created":"2026.03.24"},{"title":"Product management on the AI exponential | Claude","link":"https://claude.com/blog/product-management-on-the-ai-exponential","domain":"claude.com","tags":[],"note":"","excerpt":"Claude Code’s Head of Product Cat Wu shares how teams should rethink their workflows and roadmaps in the face of rapidly evolving model intelligence.","created":"2026.03.24"},{"title":"Harness Engineering 为什么是 Agent 时代的“控制论”？","link":"https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/SVUybMZb6uh5OCR3ceoBVA","domain":"mp.weixin.qq.com","tags":[],"note":"","excerpt":"你不必在 coding 上比机器更快，只要你能知道怎么高效地评估它的产出","created":"2026.03.24"},{"title":"I Reverse Engineered ChatGPT's Memory System, and Here's What I Found!","link":"https://manthanguptaa.in/posts/chatgpt_memory/","domain":"manthanguptaa.in","tags":["AI"],"note":"","excerpt":"When I asked ChatGPT what it remembered about me, it listed 33 facts from my name and career goals to my current fitness routine. But how does it actually store and retrieve this information? And why does it feel so seamless?\nAfter extensive experimentation, I discovered that ChatGPT’s memory system is far simpler than I expected. No vector databases. No RAG over conversation history. Instead, it uses four distinct layers: session metadata that adapts to your environment, explicit facts stored long-term, lightweight summaries of recent chats, and a sliding window of your current conversation.","created":"2026.03.23"},{"title":"I Reverse Engineered Claude's Memory System, and Here's What I Found!","link":"https://manthanguptaa.in/posts/claude_memory/","domain":"manthanguptaa.in","tags":["AI"],"note":"","excerpt":"When I reverse-engineered ChatGPT’s memory system, I found it uses pre-computed summaries injected into every prompt. But Claude’s approach is different. Through extensive experimentation, I discovered Claude uses on-demand tools and selective retrieval, a fundamentally different architecture. But how does this actually work? And how does it compare to ChatGPT’s approach?\nThis is the second post in a series where I reverse-engineer the memory systems of popular AI assistants. The first post focused on ChatGPT’s memory system. In this post, we’ll do the same exercise for Claude—and the differences are fascinating.","created":"2026.03.23"}],"total":123}</script>
